 :tx/rationale "AUDIT F-ERR-002: Error types use manual Display/Error impls — rationale is sound, document as ADR. PROBLEM: All error types use manual impl Display and impl Error instead of thiserror derives. This produces ~100 lines of boilerplate per error enum. The recovery_hint() pattern is unique and valuable — thiserror doesn't natively support per-variant recovery guidance. JUSTIFICATION: The kernel deliberately minimizes dependencies (#![forbid(unsafe_code)], no thiserror, no anyhow). The custom recovery_hint() method provides structured error guidance that aligns with NEG-INTERFACE-004 (No Error Without Recovery Hint). This is a principled design choice, not an oversight. The manual approach survives because error types are stable and rarely change. SOLUTION: Keep current approach. Document rationale as an ADR (e.g., ADR-INTERFACE-011: Manual Error Types with Recovery Hints). VERIFICATION: ADR written and indexed in docs/design/ADRS.md. DEPENDENCIES: None. This is an observation confirming existing design is correct. FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/error.rs, crates/braid/src/error.rs. SEVERITY: Low. WAVE: 1. EFFORT: 30m."
